msgid "A market enables trading with other tribes."
msgstr ""

#: addons/gauls.wad/postload.lua:46 input:46 standard
msgctxt "gauls_building"
msgid ""
"Of course hunting crocodiles is a good idea. The efficiency of hunting "
"should not increase much but the productivity can increase, if there are not "
"enough animals in the nearby forests."
msgstr ""

#. TRANSLATORS: Lore author helptext for a Gallic production site: Crocodile Hunter’s Hut
#: addons/gauls.wad/postload.lua:49 input:49 standard
msgctxt "gauls_building"
msgid "Hunter advocates the idea of building a crocodile hunter's house"
msgstr ""

#: addons/gauls.wad/postload.lua:50 input:50 standard
msgid ""
"Hunts animals to produce meat. Hunters working at this house can hunt "
"crocodiles too."
msgstr ""

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Gallic production site: Crocodile Hunter’s Hut, part 1
#: addons/gauls.wad/postload.lua:53 input:53 standard
msgctxt "gauls_building"
msgid ""
"This building is useful only when you have a Sumatran opponent and there are "
"crocodiles coming from his territory into your territory."
msgstr ""

#. TRANSLATORS: Note helptext for a Gallic production site: Crocodile Hunter’s Hut, part 2
#: addons/gauls.wad/postload.lua:55 input:55 standard
msgctxt "gauls_building"
msgid ""
"The building has 2 different working areas, the smaller for crocodile "
"hunting and the larger for game hunting."
msgstr ""

#. TRANSLATORS: Performance helptext for a Gallic production site: Crocodile Hunter’s Hut, part 1
#: addons/gauls.wad/postload.lua:59 input:59 standard
msgctxt "gauls_building"
msgid ""
"If there is a sufficient amount of crocodiles and other animals, the hunters "
"need %1$s on average to produce one meat. If there are no crocodiles, the "
"building operates as a basic hunter's hut and the hunters need %2$s on "
"average to produce one meat."
msgstr ""

